<h2 id="3order-import-statements">3.Order import statements</h2>

<p>Another features of Sass thatâ€™s widely known, <strong>@import</strong>.
This may sound insignificant at first but to not carefully ordering import statements can prove to be troubled later and it will also provide more readablity to our stylesheets. So, itâ€™s a win in every way.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-scss" data-lang="scss"><span class="k">@import</span> <span class="s1">'variables'</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="k">@import</span> <span class="s1">'partials/button'</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="k">@import</span> <span class="s1">'partials/grid'</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="k">@import</span> <span class="s1">'partials/bar'</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="k">@import</span> <span class="s1">'partials/typography'</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="k">@import</span> <span class="s1">'layouts/navigation_bar'</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="k">@import</span> <span class="s1">'layouts/footer'</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="k">@import</span> <span class="s1">'layouts/container'</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="k">@import</span> <span class="s1">'modules/forms'</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="k">@import</span> <span class="s1">'modules/cart'</span><span class="p">;</span></code></pre></figure>

